                    <p><strong>When registering on the website <a target="_blank" href="<?=$host?>"><?=$ihost?></a> or the SpinCRM mobile application, you entrust your personal data to UAB "Empera LT" (hereinafter referred to as the Company or we) and grant us the right to process them in accordance with this Policy (hereinafter referred to as the Policy) and the terms and conditions set out in <a target="_blank" href="<?=$host?>"><?=$ihost?></a> (hereinafter referred to as the Terms), as well as the conditions specified in the agreement.</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>If you do not agree with the Terms, the Agreement, this Policy, or their individual conditions, unfortunately, we will not be able to provide you with the opportunity to use any or any of the services provided by the Company (hereinafter referred to as the Services).</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>In this Policy, you will find all the information about what data we collect and process, how we use it, how long we keep it, etc. This information is important, so we hope you will read it carefully.</strong></p>
                    <p><span>Please note that both the Policy and the Terms may be changed, supplemented, or updated. The time when they come into effect is considered the moment of publication on this website.</span></p>
                    <p><b>Personal data</b><span> - any information that can be used to identify a person, as well as any information about a person who has already been identified.</span></p>
                    <p><b>We respect your privacy, and the security of your personal data is our priority. We take appropriate organizational and technical measures to ensure that your personal data is always secure and that data processing activities comply with data protection laws and our internal policies.</b></p>
                    <p><b>The Company collects and processes your personal data listed in these Terms on the following legal grounds:<br>
                    </b><span>- Your consent to the Terms and conditions set out in this Policy;<br>
                    </span><span>- Our legitimate interest;<br>
                    </span><span>- Legal obligations arising from and applicable to the Company.</span></p>
                    <p><b>One or more of the above legal grounds may apply to the processing of the same personal data, as provided for by applicable laws and conditions.</b></p>
                    <h2><span>1. What data do we process and why?</span></h2>
                    <h3><span>1.1. Registration, verification, administration, and communication</span></h3>
                    <h4><span>Registration</span></h4>
                    <p><span>By registering and agreeing to the Terms, you provide us with the following registration data. The provision of certain registration data is necessary, and without them, you will not be able to use the Services. By registering, you confirm that the personal data you provide is accurate and correct. We are not responsible for inaccurate, incomplete, or falsely provided data.</span></p>

                    <table class="table">
