                                <td><span>Information about user behavior on the </span><a target="_blank" href="<?=$host?>"><?=$ihost?></a><span> system and/or SpinCRM mobile app</span></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><span>Legal basis for data processing</span></td>
                                <td><span>Our legitimate interest to analyze data and prepare business reports needed to assess our operations and create value for both you as a customer and the Company's business</span></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><span>Term of data processing</span></td>
                                <td><span>5 years</span></td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                    <p><span>When conducting statistical data, market and customer behavior research and forming business reports needed by us, we use </span><b>automated data analysis</b><span>. During analysis we use </span><b>depersonalized data</b><span> and do not process your name, contact or other individualizing information about you. Data analysis for the purposes of statistics, market and customer behavior research allows us to make important business decisions such as the functions most commonly used by our customers, reports, etc. and other system capabilities.</span></p>
                    <p><span>Data analysis actions have no legal or similar significant impact on you.</span></p>
                    <h3><span>1.6. Klientų užklausų, skundų, prašymų ir atsiliepimų aptarnavimas</span></h3>
                    <p><span>Mes naudosime Jūsų asmens duomenis atsakydami į Jūsų užklausas, skundus, prašymus ir administruodami Jūsų atsiliepimus (toliau – </span><b>Užklausa</b><span>).</span></p>
                    <table class="table">
                        <tbody>
                            <tr style="height: 56px;">
                                <td style="height: 56px;" colspan="2"><b>Data processed for the purposes of statistics, market and customer behavior research:</b></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr style="height: 160px;">
                                <td style="height: 160px;"><span>Data categories</span></td>
                                <td style="height: 160px;"><span>Your stated identification and contact information: name, surname, telephone number, email address,</span>
                                    <p></p>
                                    <p><span>Content of your Request: the event for which you are contacting, its circumstances, date, place, your request, claim or feedback, fix an error in the system, help understand system operation principles, other information provided in the Request;</span></p>
                                    <p><span>Other documents and/or data submitted with the Request: e.g. photos, documents etc.</span></p>
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr style="height: 80px;">
                                <td style="height: 80px;"><span>Legal basis for data processing</span></td>
                                <td style="height: 80px;"><span>Fulfillment of our legal obligation to examine and respond to users' Requests, as well as our legitimate interest to evaluate customer feedback in order to improve the quality of our operations and services provided.</span></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr style="height: 80px;">
                                <td style="height: 80px;"><span>Term of data processing</span></td>
                                <td style="height: 80px;"><span>Up to 12 months</span></td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                    <p><span>We use your data only to properly and objectively examine your Request, provide you with the required information, respond to your questions, resolve your requests or claims. We may also analyze Request data to improve the quality of our operations and services provided, taking into account your opinion and suggestions.</span></p>
                    <h2><span>For how long do we process and store your data?</span></h2>
                    <p><span>We process and store your Request and related data until we examine the Request, provide you with a response and implement any decisions made, as well as for up to 6 (six) months after resolving the Request, but not less than:<br> </span><span>- Requests by email – 6 months<br> </span><span>- Complaints – 12 months<br> </span><span>- Facebook private messages – 6 months</span></p>
                    <p><span>If a legal dispute is initiated due to the Request or there is a probability of such a dispute, we may store your data longer until expiration of the legal limitation periods for filing a complaint or lawsuit and/or entry into force of the final decision.</span></p>
                    <p><span>Upon expiration of the data processing and storage period set out in this Policy, we will destroy or reliably and irreversibly anonymize your data as soon as reasonably and properly possible for such an action.</span></p>
                    <h2><span>2. From what sources do we collect your personal data?</span></h2>
                    <p><span>We receive almost all of your personal data only from you. You provide survey data to us directly, e.g. by filling out registration forms. We also receive data directly from you when you submit a Request through any of the chosen methods: by sending us an email, submitting a written request, writing through Facebook – your profile link.</span></p>
                    <p><span>If collecting additional information or conducting a significant circumstances investigation is needed to qualitatively and objectively examine your Request, we may link your Request data with data we have and/or collect when examining your Request, e.g. we may use purchase transaction data, history of use of your account, interview employees etc.</span></p>
                    <h2><span>3. In what cases and to what third parties do we disclose your data?</span></h2>
                    <p><span>We may transfer your data to third parties who assist us in providing and administering the Services, provide us with services related to administering customer Requests. Such entities may include data management service providers, data center, hosting and cloud service providers, direct marketing service providers, market research or business analytics service providers etc. In each case, we provide the data processor only with the data necessary to complete a specific assignment or provide a specific service. Our engaged data processors may process your personal data only according to our instructions and cannot use or transfer it to other persons without our consent for other purposes. Additionally, they must ensure security of your data according to applicable laws and written agreements concluded with us.</span></p>
                    <p><span>If the event described in the Request can be recognized as insurable, we will transfer your</span></p>
                    <p><span>Data may also be provided to competent public authorities or law enforcement agencies, e.g. police or supervisory institutions, but only at their request and only when required by applicable laws or in cases and manner envisaged by laws, in order to ensure our rights, security of our customers, employees and resources, submit, make and defend legal claims.</span></p>
                    <p><span>If we use a website analytics service (e.g. Google Analytics), which is applied to determine how you use information on the website <a target="_blank" href="<?=$host?>"><?=$ihost?></a> or in the SpinCRM mobile application, we may exchange your anonymized data with third parties who rely on this information when evaluating how the website or mobile application is used, preparing reports for website operators about website or mobile application activity and providing other services related to use of the website, internet and mobile application. See Cookie Policy for more details.</span></p>
                    <h2><span>4. In what territories and jurisdictions do we process your personal data?</span></h2>
                    <p><span>We process your personal data only within the territory of the European Union. We currently do not intend to transfer and do not transfer your personal data to third countries.</span></p>
                    <h2><span>5. What rights do data protection laws grant you and how can you exercise them?</span></h2>
                    <p><span>Data protection laws grant you many rights that you can freely exercise, and we must ensure you have such an ability. We provide information about your specific rights and how to exercise them further in this Policy, please read it carefully.</span></p>
                    <h3><span>5.1. Right to access the personal data we process about you</span></h3>
                    <p><span>You have the right to obtain confirmation from us whether we process personal data about you, and the right to access the personal data we process about you and information about the purposes of data processing, categories of processed data, categories of data recipients, data processing period, data sources, automated decision making.</span></p>
                    <p><span>We provide most of this information to you in this Policy and believe it is useful to you.</span></p>
                    <p><span>If you are a user of the website <a target="_blank" href="<?=$host?>"><?=$ihost?></a>, you can at any time in your account profile review the personal data we process about you (e.g. check current survey information, your provided consents), get issued invoices for you for the last 12 months. If you are a SpinCRM mobile application user, you can access all the mentioned information on the website <a target="_blank" href="<?=$host?>"><?=$ihost?></a></span></p>
                    <p><span>If the information provided in this Policy, in the website <a target="_blank" href="<?=$host?>"><?=$ihost?></a> profile or SpinCRM mobile application is insufficient for you or you wish to receive a purchase history for a period longer than 12 months, you can always contact us via the means specified in Section 6 of this Policy.</span></p>
                    <h3><span>5.2. Right to rectify personal data</span></h3>
                    <p><span>If the data you provided in our registration form has changed or you believe the information we hold about you is inaccurate or incorrect, you have the right to request this information be changed, corrected or rectified.</span></p>
                    <p><span>You can make corrections to your data in the profile of the website <a target="_blank" href="<?=$host?>"><?=$ihost?></a>. You can also contact us via the means specified in Section 6 of this Policy and ask us to rectify or update your data.</span></p>
                    <h3><span>5.3. Right to withdraw consent</span></h3>
                    <p><span>In cases where we process your data based on your consent, you have the right to withdraw your consent at any time and the data processing based on your consent will be terminated. In some cases this may mean we will no longer be able to provide the ability to continue using our Services.</span></p>
                    <p><span>For example, you can withdraw your consent to receive offers and news at any time. Withdrawing this consent will not prevent you from continuing to use the Services, but it will mean that we will not be able to provide you with useful offers.</span></p>
                    <p><span>You can adjust your consents by contacting us via the means specified in Section 6 of this Policy or by unsubscribing from newsletters using the settings indicated in the newsletter.</span></p>
                    <p><span>Upon expiration of your consent, its withdrawal or revocation, we destroy the personal data processed based on your consent in accordance with the cases specified in the Policy, and reliably and irreversibly anonymize it.</span></p>
                    <p><span>In any case, we may store the consent you have provided and evidence of it for a longer period if necessary to defend against claims, complaints or lawsuits raised against us.</span></p>
                    <h3><span>5.4. Right to lodge a complaint</span></h3>
                    <p><span>If you believe we process your data in violation of data protection law requirements, we always first ask you to contact us directly. We believe that through good faith efforts we will be able to dispel any doubts you have, satisfy requests and correct any mistakes we may have made.</span></p>
                    <p><span>If the problem resolution proposed by us does not satisfy you or, in your opinion, we will not take necessary actions according to your request, you will have the right to lodge a complaint with the supervisory authority, which in the Republic of Lithuania is the State Data Protection Inspectorate.</span></p>
                    <h3><span>5.5. Right to object to data processing based on legitimate interests</span></h3>
                    <p><span>You have the right to object to personal data processing when personal data is processed based on our legitimate interests. However, taking into account the goals of Services provision and balancing the legitimate interests of both parties (you as data subject and us as data controller), your objection may mean that by terminating data processing based on our legitimate interest we will no longer be able to provide the ability for you to continue using the Services.</span></p>
                    <p><span>To exercise the right specified in this section, please submit a written request to our Data Protection Officer.</span></p>
                    <h3><span>5.6. Right to erasure of data (right to be forgotten)</span></h3>
                    <p><span>In certain circumstances specified in data protection laws (when personal data is processed unlawfully, the basis for data processing has expired etc.), you have the right to request that we erase your personal data. To exercise this right, please submit a written request to our Data Protection Officer.</span></p>
                    <p><span>It is important to note that your survey data will be erased without your separate request, while other data - erased or reliably anonymized if you terminate use of the Services.</span></p>
                    <h3><span>5.7. Right to restrict processing</span></h3>
                    <p><span>In certain circumstances specified in data protection laws (when personal data is processed unlawfully, you dispute the accuracy of data, you have objected to data processing based on our legitimate interest etc.), you also have the right to restrict processing of your data. However, we must point out that due to restriction of data processing and during such restriction period we may not be able to ensure provision of Services to you.</span></p>
                    <p><span>To exercise the right specified in this section, please submit a written request to our Data Protection Officer.</span></p>
                    <h3><span>5.8. Right to data portability</span></h3>
                    <p><span>Data that we process based on your consent and the processing of which is carried out by automated means, you have the right to transfer to another data controller. We will provide the data you want transferred in a format commonly used in our systems and readable by computer, and at your request and if technically possible, we will transmit the data directly to another data controller specified by you.</span></p>
                    <p><span>To exercise the right to data portability, please submit a written request to our Data Protection Officer.</span></p>
                    <h3><span>5.9. Procedure for reviewing requests</span></h3>
                    <p><span>In order to protect personal data of all our customers from unlawful disclosure, upon receiving your request to provide data or implement other rights of yours, we must establish your identity. For this purpose, we may ask you to specify current survey data provided in the registration form (e.g. name, email address or phone number) and compare whether the data you specify matches the respective survey data. While carrying out this verification, we may also send a control message to the contact specified in the registration form (SMS or email), asking to perform an authorization action. If the verification procedure fails (e.g. the survey data you specify does not match the data in the registration form or you do not authorize using the received SMS or email message), we will be forced to conclude that you are not the data subject of the requested data and will have to reject your submitted request.</span></p>
                    <p><span>Upon receiving your request regarding implementation of any of your rights and having successfully completed the above verification procedure, we undertake without undue delay, but in any case no later than within one month of receiving your request and completing the verification procedure, to provide you with information about the actions taken based on your submitted request.</span></p>
                    <p><span>If your request is submitted electronically, we will also provide the response electronically, except in cases where this is impossible (e.g. due to extremely large information volume) or if you request a response in another manner.</span></p>
                    <p><span>We will refuse to satisfy your request with a motivated response when circumstances specified in laws are established, informing you thereof in writing.</span></p>
                    <h2><span>6. How and via which contacts can you contact us?</span></h2>
                    <p><span>For all data processing issues, you can contact us in the following ways:<br> </span><span>- By email info@<?=$ihost?><br> </span><span>- By phone +370 663 52000<br> </span></p>
                    <p><span>Contact details of the Data Protection Officer:<br> </span><span>Darius Vitkus, Tel. +370 663 52000<br> </span>Email address info@<?=$ihost?><span><br> </span><i><span>Address the letter as: UAB „Empera LT“, Data Protection Officer</span></i><span>.<br> </span><span><br>Our details as data controller:<br> </span><span>UAB „Empera LT“<br> </span><span>Company code </span><span>304066716</span></p>
                    <h2><span>7. How secure are your data?</span></h2>
                    <p><span>We use various security technologies and procedures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use or disclosure. Our suppliers are carefully selected, and we require them to use appropriate means capable of protecting your confidentiality and ensuring security of your personal information. However, security of information transmission via the internet or mobile communications cannot be guaranteed; any information transmission to us in the indicated ways is carried out at your own risk.</span></p>
                    <h2><span>8. Longer data retention</span></h2>
                    <p><span>Upon expiration of the data processing and retention period specified in this Policy, we destroy your data, and in cases specified in the Policy - reliably and irreversibly anonymize it, as soon as reasonably and justifiably possible considering the period required for such action, or transmit the information to you according to the specified instructions.</span></p>
                    <p><span>Longer retention of your personal data than specifically indicated in this Policy can only be carried out if:</span></p>
                    <p><span>- Necessary for us to defend against claims, complaints or lawsuits and implement our rights;<br> </span><span>- There are reasonable suspicions of unlawful conduct under investigation;<br> </span><span>- Your data is essential for proper resolution of disputes, complaints;<br> </span><span>- For backup copies and similar purposes;<br> </span><span>- For other grounds foreseen in laws.</span></p>
                    <h2><span>9. Cookies</span></h2>
                    <p><span>We use cookies (a small information file sent to your computer or other device (e.g. mobile phone) when you visit our website and stored in your browser. A cookie is sent to your computer or other device in order to store data and enable us to recognize you as a Services user when you revisit our website. Cookies also allow us to associate your purchase history and other data collected during your use of Services with your internet browsing. Information collected via cookies enables us to ensure more convenient browsing for you, provide appealing offers and learn more about website user behavior, analyze trends and improve both the website and your service.</span></p>
                    <p><span>Our website also uses third-party cookies. These cookies are used to create a browsing history for each visitor in order to provide the best experience on our website. If your browser allows saving of third-party cookies, our selected partner has the ability to save its cookies onto your browser.</span></p>
                    <h2><span>10. Applicability and amendments of the Policy</span></h2>
                    <p><span>This Policy is effective from May 25, 2018. If we amend this Policy, we will publish its updated version on this page.</span></p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
